# APE fork provenance

Upstream: https://github.com/Attempto/APE
Base pin: 5f4d5354a45fb772763bf1a9543f508f15b28982
License: LGPL-3.0-or-later. The upstream `LICENSE.txt` is retained verbatim in this directory.

## Fork pin

The vendored fork identity (the "fork pin") is the base pin plus the ordered `patches/` set plus the SHA-256 tree manifest `MANIFEST.sha256`.

Patches MUST be git-format patches named `NNNN-<slug>.patch`, applied in lexical order on top of the base pin. Each patch MUST be minimal and independently re-applicable. The ordered patch set is currently empty.

Any patch that modifies an upstream file MUST add a prominent in-file modification notice with a relevant date. LGPL-3.0-or-later incorporates GPL-3.0 §5(a), which requires such notices for modified files; the notice MUST travel in the same ordered patch set as the modification. This contract mirrors the prominent in-file notices carried by `vendor/e--/patches/0004-add-apache-modification-notices.patch`.

The vendored upstream file tree is byte-identical to the base pin plus this ordered patch set.

Any APE change MUST pass the "bump fork pin" gate: update the patch set, regenerate `MANIFEST.sha256`, and update `docs/provenance.md`.

## Trust posture

APE is trusted parser input to the compilation pipeline, but it is not part of the Python TCB. It runs in a separate SWI-Prolog process; Python moves bytes only. The narrow first-party adapter lands in M2.2 and does not change this boundary.

## Regression lexicon

The full Clex lexicon is GPL-3.0 and EXCLUDED from the repository, product, vendor tree, and distributions. Regression testing may fetch only the pinned file `clex_lexicon.pl` from commit `20960a5ce07776cb211a8cfb25dc8c81fcdf25e2` into gitignored `.scratch/`; it MUST never be committed or vendored. The pinned raw file is:

